> To avoid locale controversies I suggest a simple half width space.

@calmh Sounds good to me, probably also looks quite tidy and modern

> What do you think about limiting the displayed numbers to 4 digits

@imsodin Even though your suggestion makes sence for file sizes, it might not be best for the amount of files and folders. I sometimes check the last digit(s) in order to see if Syncthing has detected the new file I just added. Say, the number is ...65 and I copy something from a USB stick to a shared folder, I wait for the number to increase. It's lazier than looking for the right shared folder on the left hand side (I have dozens in the list) and opening it.
